contentrichtext.text: '''Dogtown''' may refer to {{TOC right}} == Places == ;Canada * Former name of [[Okanagan Falls, British Columbia]], derived from the name of Skaha (Dog) Lake ;United States * [[Dogtown, Alabama]] * [[Dogtown, California (disambiguation)]], several places * [[Dogtown, Massachusetts]], a ghost town * [[Dogtown, St. Louis]], Irish section comprising several neighborhoods * The [[Clayton/Tamm, St. Louis]] neighborhood == Films, music and television == * [[Dogtown (film)|''Dogtown'' (film)]], a 1997 film * [[Dogtown (song)|"Dogtown" (song)]], a song by [[Harry Chapin]] * ''[[Dogtown and Z-Boys]]'', a 2001 documentary film about skateboarding * ''[[Lords of Dogtown]]'', a 2005 film based on ''Dogtown and Z-Boys'' * Dogtown Records, a record label established by musician [[Byard Lancaster]], active in the 1970s * ''[[DogTown]]'', a National Geographic Channel series ==See also== * ''[[Dogville]]'', a 2003 movie starring Nicole Kidman * [[Dogtooth (disambiguation)]] {{disambiguation|geo}}
